    <stitle>REYCO 101A, 102, 102W SUSPENSIONS - ASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s03005s_5.xml" xrefid="f0300507">Figure 7</hotlnk>for all Items in parentheses.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="0">
            <title>SUSPENSION ASSEMBLIES</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the shoulder bolts in the spring brackets and equalizer brackets. Tighten the
                    shoulder bolt nuts as specified in the
                    <hotlnk document="s03005s_12.xml" xrefid="hl0300502">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the axle seat (Item 29) on the assembled leaf spring. Secure it with the
                    U-bolts, U-bolt washers and nuts (Items 24, 31 and 32) and the U-bolt plate (Item 30). Loosely
                    tighten the U-bolt nuts.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Final-tighten U-bolts nuts to the value found in the
                            <hotlnk document="s03005s_12.xml" xrefid="hl0300502">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>, when weight of
                            vehicle is back on the wheels.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the torque arms in the front and rear spring brackets (Items 7 and 20), the
                    equalizer mounting bracket (Item 9), and axle seats (Item 29). Install the torque arm bolts (Items
                    18 and 33), washers (Item 5), and loosely tighten the retaining nuts (Item 28).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Perform suspension alignment before tightening the retaining nuts to the value found in
                    the
                    <hotlnk document="s03005s_12.xml" xrefid="hl0300502">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the vehicle wheels.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the suspension before returning the vehicle to service.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Refer to Group 03 - SUSPENSION, ALIGNMENT section in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual
                            for alignment information.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Schedule the vehicle for inspection and maintenance to retighten the spring U-bolts at
                    recommended intervals. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s03005s_2.xml" xrefid="hl0300501">MAINTENANCE</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
